        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "Earnings call summarizes the financial performance of a company , \r",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "and it is an important indicator of the future financial risks of the company . <S>\r",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "We quantitatively study how earnings calls are correlated with the financial risks , with a special focus on the financial crisis of 2009 . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "In particular , we perform a text regression task : \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "given the transcript of an earnings call , \r",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "we predict the volatility of stock prices from the week \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "after the call is made . <S>\r",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "We propose the use of copula : \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "a powerful statistical framework \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "that separately models the uniform marginals and their complex multivariate stochastic dependencies , \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "while not requiring any prior assumptions on the distributions of the covariate and the dependent variable . <S>\r",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "By performing probability integral transform , \r",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "our approach moves beyond the standard count-based bag-of-words models in NLP , \r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "and improves previous work on text regression \r",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "by incorporating the correlation among local features in the form of semiparametric Gaussian copula . <S>\r",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "In experiments , we show \r",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "that our model significantly outperforms strong linear and non-linear discriminative baselines on three datasets under various settings . <S>\r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        }
    ]
